<subSubSection id="1240C5C4FFECF15DCAA2F23DD2E8B9F2" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="type">
<paragraph id="3129E2D9BF08F1EB8D5BEA0F51DE6EC7" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="47543FAEB2F054FEACA383CADB4AE085" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Based on 
<taxonomicName id="C0FBA73C5A7714528C08AA15B1EBD00A" authorityName="Wood &amp; Williams &amp; Mitchell &amp; Carine &amp; Harris &amp; Scotland" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus ruspolii" order="Solanales" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruspolii">
<emphasis id="D3A76D3635C4EEEC4B0603B4CEA95A1B" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Convolvulus ruspolii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dammer ex Hall f.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5960F503ABB74123C37D0ED4A9FC5E66" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="distinguishing features">
<paragraph id="D18666E75C75597AB8339F07B86D9DE2" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Distinguishing features.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="088FEEFE492C504DB25124845896D038" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="E7BB21C59A75D2107ACDD15BBCC3383C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. hystrix" order="Solanales" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="ruspolii" subSpecies="hystrix">subsp. hystrix</taxonomicName>
in armature but the spine-like side branches rather slender. Stems glabrous to shortly pubescent. Leaves 5-11 
<normalizedToken id="4C7940BE46BE475FAFFEB6A1AA46606E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 mm, oblong or lanceolate to elliptic, glabrous to puberulent or sericeous. Flowers usually solitary, sometimes in pairs forming a narrowly oblong-lanceolate head twice as long as broad; bracteoles 3-3.5 
<normalizedToken id="D63EAAD9B6CEB9C9FCB8C5F5E3CAB36E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-1.5 mm, oblong, oblanceolate or obovate, longer than broad; corolla 0.8-1 cm long. [
<bibRefCitation id="A639CF27F3442681704E7B63DA9DC0F9" author="Sebsebe, D" editor="Hedberg, I" journalOrPublisher="National Herbarium Addis Ababa University &amp; Department of Systematic Botany, Uppsala University" pageId="211" pageNumber="212" pagination="161 - 231" refId="B330" refString="Sebsebe, D, 2006. Convolvulaceae. In: Hedberg, I, Ensermu, K, Edwards, S, Sebsebe, Demissew, Persson, E, Eds., Flora of Ethiopia &amp; Eritrea 5: Gentianaceae to Cyclocheilaceae. National Herbarium Addis Ababa University &amp; Department of Systematic Botany, Uppsala University: 161 - 231" title="Convolvulaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of Ethiopia &amp; Eritrea 5: Gentianaceae to Cyclocheilaceae." year="2006">Sebsebe 2006</bibRefCitation>
: 182]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4F81AAD0A9D19B5A32F7F33924D704A6" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="AA5D84817F059C3E86C2819E02623FEF" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B2D9ECF6A7E86F3EA6C9B16CAF840941" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Ogaden region of Ethiopia (
<emphasis id="02CFF1EE24C20A9624927DD436C7CE68" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Hemming</emphasis>
1530) and Somalia (
<emphasis id="928E17B7F5F6C892FE5961E2215D85AC" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Popov</emphasis>
1008; 
<emphasis id="472E6E84502D58EE39978592B262B4E7" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Glover &amp; Gilliland</emphasis>
636; 
<emphasis id="F3B605CD856F040C8811E54FF8978EA6" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Thulin &amp; Warfa</emphasis>
5562; 
<emphasis id="269E3F5AC6E2C59D36094409147E2A6F" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Bally</emphasis>
10164).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="19436AA5D9231D942061D3552AEF8AC7" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="notes">
<paragraph id="5B58A0BC5395B780B9BBC0359E943896" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="60760FCF091331A435F93E7E54EBB8FA" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Some specimens from Somalia (
<emphasis id="EA43C512C6D45E67CB983FFAFDA407AD" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Gillett, Hemming &amp; Watson</emphasis>
21885, 
<emphasis id="65E08A9FAC7453F99ACFBFBA8D908D8E" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Bally &amp; Melville</emphasis>
16271, 
<emphasis id="B7919E7EFE7B7F49326D6D386074BFF5" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Thulin &amp; Warfa</emphasis>
5562, 
<emphasis id="9BD7DF047AC9B89ADAE38E44BF6CB2D8" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Kasmi et al.</emphasis>
850) have ellipsoid flower clusters with 2-4 flowers and are intermediate with 
<taxonomicName id="B95C882AE4C20960C7ED21CDDBB56CF1" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. hystrix" order="Solanales" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="ruspolii" subSpecies="hystrix">subsp. hystrix</taxonomicName>
and suggestive of hybrid origin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
